  m_Name: Patella_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Patella_R
  partName: Patella Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right patella is a sesamoid bone located within the tendon of the quadriceps
    muscle at the front of the canine stifle joint. It functions primarily to improve
    leverage and mechanical efficiency during extension of the hindlimb.The patella
    also protects the stifle joint and guides movement of  the quadriceps tendon
    over the femur during locomotion.
  - Proper alignment of the patella is essential for stable joint mechanics, balanced
    weight distribution, and efficient hindlimb movement. It plays an important role
    in walking, running, jumping, and maintaining posture.
